  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Some geth peers disconnect from us on a frequent basis when we're doing a fast-sync, and they seem to do so because they're trying to fetch chain data from us and when we fail to respond too many times, they disconnect. See https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/7cf83cee5240f76bdf8ff4f1024643fd126e1018/eth/downloader/downloader.go#L1083-L1090 and https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/7cf83cee5240f76bdf8ff4f1024643fd126e1018/eth/downloader/downloader.go#L866-L869\r\n\r\nI don't think there's much we can do about it as during a fast-sync we most likely won't have the data the peer is asking for, but thought I'd create this issue because others are likely to notice this as well.",
